---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import siteContent from '../../content/site.en.json';

const lang = 'en';
---

<MainLayout
  title={`Privacy Policy | ${siteContent.company}`}
  description="Privacy Policy for Force Field — how we collect, use, and protect your personal data."
  lang={lang}
>
  <Header lang={lang} content={siteContent} />
  
  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-secondary-900 to-secondary-800 py-16">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-primary-500/20 text-primary-400 text-sm font-medium mb-6">
            <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
            </svg>
            Privacy &amp; Compliance
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-secondary-300">
            Force Field takes your privacy and the security of personal data very seriously.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-padding">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
          
          <div class="mb-8 p-6 rounded-xl bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border border-primary-200 dark:border-primary-800">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary-500 text-white flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400">
                  <strong class="text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Last Updated:</strong> February 9, 2026<br />
                  <strong class="text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Legal Entity:</strong> 9558-6616 Québec Inc.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
            
            <!-- Introduction -->
            <div class="not-prose mb-10 p-6 rounded-xl bg-secondary-900 dark:bg-secondary-800 text-white">
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-primary-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
                </svg>
                Welcome
              </h2>
              <p class="text-secondary-300 mb-0">
                Thank you for your interest in Force Field. We hope that you will enjoy using our "Services", which include: (i) visiting our website at <a href="https://datasciencetech.ca/en/" class="text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300">https://datasciencetech.ca/en/</a>, including all subpages and subdomains, present and future (the "Website"); and (ii) the use of our firewall "Solution" which is a platform and AI-powered tool consisting in a security layer that sits between End Users and LLM-powered knowledge systems.
              </p>
            </div>

            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Force Field takes your privacy and the security of personal data very seriously. We are providing this privacy policy (the "Policy") to tell you about who we are, what personal data we collect from you and about you, and what we do with your personal data, all while you use the Services or otherwise interact with us online. The Policy also explains your rights under applicable law, how you can contact us and the necessary authorities to enforce those rights. We ask that you please read it carefully.
            </p>

            <!-- Key Elements -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Key Elements of this Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Here are the key elements of this Policy so that you can know the important parts right away to make an informed decision about your consent for our collection, use and disclosure of your personal data. By submitting any personal data to us via any means, you consent to such collection, use and disclosure.
            </p>
            <div class="not-prose mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-secondary-200 dark:border-secondary-700">
              <table class="w-full text-sm">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="bg-secondary-100 dark:bg-secondary-800">
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Personal data we collect</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">What we do with it</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Third parties we share it with</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-secondary-200 dark:divide-secondary-700">
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium">Account Information</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Create and verify your account</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Companies that provide the technical infrastructure for the Solution; companies that manage our email and communications</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium">Data Inputs/Prompts</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Process data inputs and prompts to allow you to fully use and test the Solution</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Companies that provide the technical infrastructure for the Solution</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>

            <!-- Definitions -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Some Terms</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              <strong>"Data Protection Laws"</strong> refers to the laws that are designed to protect your personal data and privacy in the place where you live. Force Field is committed to adhering to all applicable Data Protection Laws, which include:
            </p>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              <li>The <strong>"GDPR"</strong>, the European Data Protection Law (Regulation (EU) 2016/679);</li>
              <li>The <strong>"UK GDPR"</strong> which applies to our activities in the United Kingdom;</li>
              <li><strong>"PIPEDA"</strong> (Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act), the Canadian Data Protection Law;</li>
              <li>Quebec's Act Respecting the Protection of Personal Information in the Private Sector (the <strong>"Quebec Privacy Act"</strong>), as amended by Law 25;</li>
              <li>The <strong>"CCPA"</strong> (California Consumer Privacy Act), as amended by the California Privacy Rights Act; and</li>
              <li>Any other state privacy laws in force in the United States, such as those currently in force in Colorado, Connecticut, and Virginia.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              <strong>"Personal data"</strong> is information that we collect from you or about you and which is defined in the GDPR as "any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person." Under PIPEDA, the Quebec Privacy Act and the CCPA, the equivalent concept is "personal information." Any mention of "personal data" in this Policy will also mean personal information.
            </p>

            <!-- About Us -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">About Us; Contacting Us</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              9558-6616 Québec Inc. (referred to throughout this Policy as "Force Field"), which owns and operates the Website and the Solution, is a Quebec corporation located in the province of Quebec, Canada. Where this Policy refers to "Force Field", it may refer to 9558-6616 Québec Inc. and/or its affiliates, and their respective Representatives, depending on the context.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              The Solution is primarily intended for use by enterprise clients (each, a "User") and will be accessible to each User's employees and consultants (the "End Users") via the User's own internal LLM-powered knowledge system.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Under the GDPR, Force Field is generally a "data controller." Under PIPEDA, Force Field is an "organization" and, under the Quebec Privacy Act, Force Field is an "enterprise."
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg bg-secondary-100 p-6 dark:bg-secondary-800">
              <p class="text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">
                <strong>Force Field Privacy and Data Protection Officer</strong><br />
                Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@datasciencetech.ca" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">privacy@datasciencetech.ca</a><br /><br />
                <strong>Mailing Address:</strong><br />
                700-465 McGill Street<br />
                Montreal, Quebec<br />
                H2Y 2H1<br />
                Canada
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Your Rights -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Your Rights</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              You have the following rights regarding your personal data held by Force Field. Please note that not necessarily all of these rights may be available to you; this depends on the Data Protection Laws where you are located. Exercising certain of these rights may affect your ability to use a part or the entirety of the Services:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              <li>The right to <strong>withdraw your consent</strong> for Force Field to process your personal data at any time;</li>
              <li>The right to have your personal data <strong>erased</strong> from Force Field's records;</li>
              <li>The right to have your name <strong>de-indexed</strong> from the Website or the Solution;</li>
              <li>The right to <strong>access</strong> your personal data and any relevant information around its processing and use;</li>
              <li>The right to have a copy of your personal data given to you in an <strong>easy-to-read format</strong> (data portability);</li>
              <li>The right to have your personal data <strong>corrected or updated</strong>;</li>
              <li>The right to <strong>opt out</strong> of email marketing communications;</li>
              <li>The right to <strong>know</strong> whether Force Field shares your personal data (and if so, who gets it);</li>
              <li>The right to demand that Force Field <strong>not sell</strong> your personal data (Force Field does not sell your personal data);</li>
              <li>The right to <strong>restrict</strong> the processing of your personal data if it is inaccurate or if processing is against the law; and</li>
              <li>The right to <strong>refuse</strong> any marketing or advertising targeted at you.</li>
            </ul>

            <!-- Data Collected -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Limited Personal Data Collected from You</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Force Field limits the amount of personal data we collect to what is necessary and appropriate for the identified purposes. We will not use or disclose your personal data for purposes other than those for which it was collected, except with your consent or as permitted by applicable law.
            </p>
            <div class="not-prose mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-secondary-200 dark:border-secondary-700">
              <table class="w-full text-sm">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="bg-secondary-100 dark:bg-secondary-800">
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Category</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Data processed</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Purpose</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Legal basis (GDPR)</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-secondary-200 dark:divide-secondary-700">
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium">Account Information</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">First name, last name, email address</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">1. Create and verify your Solution account<br />2. Manage the account, give access to Solution features and enable logging in</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Your consent</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium">Data Inputs/Prompts</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Any personal data submitted to or collected by the LLM-powered knowledge system supported by the Solution</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Allow you to use and test the Solution as intended</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Your consent</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>

            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Personal Data Collected from Third Parties</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              We do not collect any personal data about you from third parties. However, your use of the Solution is in connection with an LLM-powered knowledge system. The LLM service provider behind that system (such as OpenAI or Anthropic) is a third party to Force Field and will also receive any personal data that you submit to the LLM-powered knowledge system.
            </p>

            <!-- Data Sharing -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Who We Transfer Your Personal Data To</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              We only share some of your personal data with third parties identified below. Each type of third party is under a contractual obligation not to (1) transfer or sell your personal data; or (2) use your personal data for any purpose other than those identified.
            </p>
            <div class="not-prose mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-secondary-200 dark:border-secondary-700">
              <table class="w-full text-sm">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="bg-secondary-100 dark:bg-secondary-800">
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Category</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Third parties</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">What they do</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-secondary-200 dark:divide-secondary-700">
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium" rowspan="2">Account Information</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Companies that provide technical infrastructure and hosting services (e.g., Google Cloud)</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Store it; keep it for record-keeping purposes</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Companies that help us send emails (e.g., SendGrid and Google Workspace)</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Send you emails as detailed in the Email Communications section</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium">Data Inputs/Prompts</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Companies that provide technical infrastructure and hosting services (e.g., Google Cloud)</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">Store it temporarily</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300 mt-4">
              We will share personal data with law enforcement or other public authorities if required by applicable law, to investigate illegal activities, to address abuse, or as required under any applicable law. We may also share personal data to affiliates under common control, or in the event of a merger, reorganization or sale of assets. <strong>We do not sell or rent your personal data to any third party.</strong>
            </p>

            <!-- Sensitive Info -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Sensitive Personal Information</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              We do not collect any of what the Data Protection Laws consider sensitive personal information from you when you visit the Website or use the Solution, unless you voluntarily submit it to us, which we encourage you not to do.
            </p>

            <!-- Email -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Email Communications and Compliance with Anti-Spam Laws</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Force Field uses SendGrid and Gmail via Google Workspace to (i) verify your email when you sign up for an account; (ii) email you with updates or notifications regarding the Solution; and (iii) respond to your communications. Force Field's email practices are designed to be compliant with anti-spam laws, specifically CASL (Canada's Anti-Spam Law) and the American CAN-SPAM Act.
            </p>

            <!-- Statistical -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Limited Gathering of Information for Statistical and Security Purposes</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Force Field automatically collects certain technical metadata about the Solution and its Users and End Users, but none of this information identifies you personally, except via an alphanumeric string. For example, we temporarily collect IP addresses when requests are submitted to the Solution. This metadata may be used (i) to trace fraudulent or criminal activity; (ii) for auditing, operational monitoring and session tracking; and (iii) to produce general usage metrics.
            </p>

            <!-- Cookies -->
            <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-6 rounded-xl bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border border-primary-200 dark:border-primary-800">
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 flex items-center gap-2 text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">
                <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-primary-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                </svg>
                Tracking Technology ("Cookies")
              </h2>
              <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300 mb-0">
                Force Field only uses <strong>functional and essential cookies</strong> in connection with the Website. Your browser can be set to refuse cookies or delete them after they have been accepted and stored.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Protection -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">How We Protect Your Personal Data</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              We have implemented strict technical and organizational procedures for ensuring that, by default, only personal data which are necessary for each specific purpose are processed by us. These procedures prevent your personal data from being lost or used or accessed in any unauthorized way.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Force Field uses only industry best practices in keeping any data collected secure. We use third-party vendors and hosting partners that have been selected for their high standards of security. For example, Force Field uses <strong>Google Cloud</strong>, a recognized leader in secure data with a robust security program, for hosting of the Solution. When you use our Website or the Solution, your connection is protected with <strong>HTTPS (TLS)</strong>.
            </p>

            <!-- Internal Policies -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Internal Procedures and Policies</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              In addition to the technical measures described above, we have drafted and implemented internal procedures and policies regarding personal data, including:
            </p>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              <li>A framework for the keeping and destruction of personal data, including anonymized data;</li>
              <li>Defining roles and responsibilities of Force Field personnel throughout the life cycle of personal data;</li>
              <li>A process for dealing with individual complaints and requests for personal data and exercising of rights under Data Protection Laws; and</li>
              <li>A management and IT policy for addressing potential data breach incidents.</li>
            </ol>

            <!-- EEA/UK Transfers -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Transfer of Your Personal Data Outside of the EEA and the U.K.</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              For our European users, we endeavour to keep personal data inside the EEA or the U.K. Transfers are limited to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              <li><strong>Canada:</strong> Determined to have an "adequate level of protection" under European data protection law.</li>
              <li><strong>The United States:</strong> Only to companies that are GDPR-compliant and have concluded the Standard Contractual Clauses for the transfer of personal data outside the EEA and the U.K.</li>
            </ul>

            <!-- Quebec Transfers -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Transfer of Your Personal Data Outside of Quebec</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              For our Quebec Users, End Users and Website visitors, we endeavour to keep your personal data in Quebec. When transfers occur, we:
            </p>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              <li>Perform a Privacy Impact Assessment (PIA) prior to data leaving Quebec, as required by the Quebec Privacy Act; and</li>
              <li>If the PIA allows the transfer, sign a Data Processing Agreement (DPA) with the service provider that adheres to the requirements of the Quebec Privacy Act.</li>
            </ol>

            <!-- Supervisory Authorities -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Supervisory Authorities and Complaints</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              If you are in the EEA or the U.K., under the GDPR, you have the right to make a complaint to the appropriate supervisory authority. If you are in the U.K., contact the <strong>Information Commissioner's Office</strong> (0303 123 1113). If you are in France, contact the <strong>Commission Nationale de l'Informatique et des Libertés</strong>.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg bg-secondary-100 p-6 dark:bg-secondary-800">
              <p class="text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">
                <strong>In Canada:</strong> <a href="https://www.priv.gc.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada</a><br />
                <strong>In Québec:</strong> <a href="https://www.cai.gouv.qc.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">Commission d'accès à l'information du Québec</a>
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Data Retention -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Data Retention and Anonymization</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Your personal data will only be kept for as long as it is necessary for the purpose needed. For example, we will retain your account information for as long as you have an active account. We may keep data for a longer period to satisfy legal requirements or to protect our legal interests. In some cases, where permitted, we may keep anonymized data for legitimate business purposes.
            </p>

            <!-- Automated Decision-Making -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Automated Decision-Making</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Force Field does not use any automated decision-making processes with regard to your personal data in providing the Website or the Solution.
            </p>

            <!-- Children -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Our Services are only intended for persons who have reached the age of majority in their respective jurisdictions. We do not knowingly collect any personal data from a child under the minimum ages. If we become aware that we have inadvertently received personal data from a person under the minimum ages, we will delete such information from our records.
            </p>

            <!-- Changes -->
            <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-900 dark:text-white">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-300">
              Because Data Protection Laws are constantly evolving, every now and then we will have to update this Policy. We will post a prominent notice on the Website and the Solution's platform page if we make significant changes.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-8 text-secondary-500 dark:text-secondary-500 text-sm">
              &copy; (under license) 9558-6616 Québec Inc., 2026
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer lang={lang} content={siteContent} />
</MainLayout>
